gomodel:SYNGO_3022  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 4: Inhibition of synaptic clustering of PSD-95 but not of NMDA receptors by Antp-CRIPT.\n\nFigure 5: Quantitation of Antp-CRIPT effects on PSD-95, chapsyn-110, GKAP, CRIPT and NMDA receptor clustering.\n- \"In contrast to its severe inhibition of the clustering of PSD-95, chapsyn-110 and GKAP, Antp-CRIPT had no significant effect on the pattern or density of synaptophysin clusters in cultured hippocampal neurons (Figs. 4a and 5a and b). \"\n\n27/3/2018 Pim\n- CRIPT may be a 'structural constituent of the PSD' but until now I think there is too little data to support this claim.. Experimental description: - \"For biochemical experiments, rat hippocampal cultures were prepared using described methods\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2018-03-27" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_3022" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .
